# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: bclib: memory-safety bugs
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* DONE [#A] bclib: memory-safety bugs  :critical:bclib:memory:
  RESOLUTION (2026-06-20):
  - BcMem_Clear/Fill/Copy: replaced the hand-rolled word-at-a-time loops (whose
    alignment masks and mod-2-only copy congruence caused misaligned CARD32
    access) with memset/memset/memmove. Correct, alignment-safe, overlap-safe.
  - BcCStr_RepeatChar: clamp count to [0,1023] BEFORE the cache fast-path.
  - BcCStr_Terminate: drop the stray buffer[length+1]=0 (overran buffer[1024]
    at length==1023); pass length+1 to BcCStr_Assign so it copies up to `length`
    chars as documented and terminates correctly.
  - BcList_RemoveObjectAt: loop while idx+1<count (was idx<count, reading
    elements[count]); SetCapacity now rejects a newCapacity whose byte size
    would overflow the CARD32 alloc argument.
  - BcString: DeleteFromLength rejects delen<=0; PositionFrom bounds the inner
    match by sub->dlength (the tail-match 0==0 over-read); CopyFromLength clamps
    idx to [0,str->dlength].
  Validated with functional tests (position exact/mid/none/longer-needle/from-idx,
  list remove first+last at capacity, overlapping BcMem_Copy, fill/clear).

Severity: *high/critical* — out-of-bounds accesses and undefined behaviour.

** Findings

*** [high] BcMem_Clear / BcMem_Fill: wrong alignment test → misaligned CARD32 access (BcMem.c:105-128,151-174)
The alignment checks mask with =((CARDPTR)p) & (CARDPTR)sizeof(T)= instead of
=& (sizeof(T)-1)=. For CARD16 that tests bit 1 (=addr & 2=), not "is the address
odd" (=addr & 1=). An address with =addr&1==1= but =addr&2==0= skips the
byte/half-word pre-alignment and then dereferences a =CARD32*= / =CARD16*= at a
misaligned address: UB, and a fault on strict-alignment targets.
Fix: mask with =(sizeof(T)-1)=.

*** [high] BcMem_Copy: insufficient alignment handling (BcMem.c:190,211-247)
The "same parity" branch compares only =from&1 == to&1= and then aligns/advances
on =((CARDPTR)from)&3= using the *original* =from= (never the advancing
pointer), so the byte-prefix loop terminates wrong and two pointers congruent
mod 2 but not mod 4 still reach a misaligned =CARD32*= dereference.
Fix: require =from= and =to= congruent mod 4 before the word loop, and align
using the moving pointer; otherwise fall back to byte copy.

*** [high] BcCStr_Terminate: writes past terminator / one byte past buffer (BcCStr.c:127)
After =BcCStr_Assign= already NUL-terminates, the extra =buffer[length+1]=0;=
leaves =buffer[length]= as garbage *inside* the returned string and writes at
=length+1= (=buffer[1024]= when =length==1023=). Fix: drop the extra line (or
terminate once at the correct index and size the buffer accordingly).

*** [high] BcCStr_RepeatChar: unclamped index in cache fast-path (BcCStr.c:96-99)
The fast path =if((count<=oldcount)&&(c==oldc))= runs *before* =count= is
clamped to [0,1023]; a negative =count= reaches =buffer[count]=0;= (negative
index, OOB write). Fix: clamp =count= before the cache check.

*** [medium] BcList_RemoveObjectAt: reads one element past the array (BcList.c:261-264)
=while(idx<plist->count){ elements[idx]=elements[idx+1]; idx++; }= reads
=elements[count]= when =idx==count-1= (OOB when the array is full) and does one
useless copy. Fix: loop while =idx+1<count=.
(Confirmed; same pattern exists in bplib and bolib — see those issues.)

*** [medium] BcString bounds / sign issues (BcString.c)
- =BcString_CopyFromLength= (~343): only the upper bound is clamped; a negative
  =idx= or =idx>dlength= leads to an OOB =BcMem_Copy=. Validate =0<=idx<=dlength=.
- =BcString_DeleteFromLength= (~295): negative =delen= not rejected; =idx+delen=
  can overflow INT32 and produce an over-long copy. Require =delen>=0=.
- =BcString_PositionFrom= (~315-326): inner match loop is not bounded by
  =sub->dlength=; it relies on NUL terminators and over-reads on a tail match.
  Bound =i= by =sub->dlength=.

*** [medium] Unchecked size arithmetic in BcList growth (BcList.c:197,229,312; alloc at 75/141)
=2*capacity=, =count+other->count=, and =sizeof(void*)*newCapacity= can wrap
CARD32, yielding a too-small allocation then OOB writes. Add overflow checks
before doubling/multiplying. (Needs very large lists on 64-bit, but real.)

** Plan
1. Fix the alignment masks in BcMem (use =sizeof-1=); add a misaligned-buffer test.
2. Fix the two BcCStr OOB writes; clarify the size/length contract (see doc-content-gaps).
3. Fix BcList_RemoveObjectAt bound and add overflow guards on growth.
4. Add lower-bound/overflow validation to the three BcString functions.
5. Run the test suite under AddressSanitizer/UBSan to confirm.
